cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.SI 

This paper is primarily focused on designing incentive mechanisms for improving the performance of crowdsourced mobile video streaming. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes auction mechanisms for selling opportunities for downloading video segments with multiple bitrates, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper deals with multi-bitrate coded videos, which is related to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the challenges of designing incentive mechanisms for asynchronous downloading behaviors, which is related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the real-world performance of the proposed mechanism, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
